FLINK SETUP.

SETUP KAFKA:
  1. Download apache kafka Binary Download -> https://kafka.apache.org/community/downloads/
  -  kafka_2.12-3.7.1.tgz
  
  2. cd ~
  - tar -xvzf ~/Downloads/kafka_2.12-3.7.1.tgz
  
  3. Add these exports to ~/.bashrc:
  
  export KAFKA_HOME=$HOME/kafka_2.12-3.7.1
  export PATH=$KAFKA_HOME/bin:$PATH 
  
  4. source ~/.bashrc
  
  5. cd ~/kafka_2.12-3.7.1/
  
  6. In Terminal 1: Run: zookeeper-server-start.sh config/zookeeper.properties
  
  7. In Terminal 2: kafka-server-start.sh config/server.properties
  
  8. In Terminal 3: kafka-topics.sh --create --topic sales --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --partitions 3 --replication-factor 1 
  
  9. In Terminal 4: python3 producer.py


SETUP FLINK
1. 
Create Virtual Env. In appropriate directory
- RUN: python3.9 -m venv flink_env
- RUN: source flink_env/bin/activate


2. 
Check java version using (java -version). If its not 21, download openjdk@21 
- RUN: brew update
- RUN: brew install openjdk@21
- RUN: sudo ln -sfn $(brew --prefix openjdk@21)/libexec/openjdk.jdk /Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/openjdk-21.jdk
- RUN: vim ~/.bashrc
- Add the following to ~/.bashrc or ~/.zshrc. Save and exit by clicking :x. 
  export JAVA_HOME="$(/usr/libexec/java_home -v 21)"
  export PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:$PATH"
- source ~/.bashrc
- RUN: java -version - SEE OUTPUT

openjdk version "21.0.10" 2026-01-20
OpenJDK Runtime Environment (build 21.0.10+7-Ubuntu-122.04)
OpenJDK 64-Bit Server VM (build 21.0.10+7-Ubuntu-122.04, mixed mode, sharing)


3. 
Download PY Apache-flink: 
- pip install --upgrade pip setuptools wheel
- pip install --force-reinstall setuptools==65.5.0
- pip install --no-build-isolation apache-flink==1.18.0

4. 
Download flink and scala bin: 
- cd ~ 
- wget https://archive.apache.org/dist/flink/flink-1.18.0/flink-1.18.0-bin-scala_2.12.tgz
- tar -xzf flink-1.18.0-bin-scala_2.12.tgz
- vim ~/.bashrc
- Add the following 2 vars:
  export FLINK_HOME=$HOME/flink-1.18.0
  export PATH=$FLINK_HOME/bin:$PATH
- source ~/.bashrc

5. 
Download flink sql connector
- Go to website: https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/apache/flink/flink-sql-connector-kafka/3.0.1-1.18/
- flink-sql-connector-kafka-3.0.1-1.18.jar
- copy this jar to $FLINK_HOME/lib


6. RUN: python flink_consumer.py




